(158, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 77, 'en', 'The development of Lapang Museum, which is located in Banjarejo Village, Gabus Sub-district, Grobogan Regency, is a form of preserving cultural heritage that consists of animal fossils as a part of ancient human civilization and it can support science and history knowledge renewal in Indonesia. Lapang Museum is a tourist attraction that presents a place of fossils discovery which are elephants, buffalos, crocodiles, hippopotamus, rhinos, deer, wolves, sharks, turtles, and bulls. In addition, there is also the discovery of a site with a pair of bricks in it that indicates a relic oaf large and historic buildings. Ancient objects conserved in Lapang Museum include tools from ceramic, gold jewelry, kris and other types of heirlooms, as well as former oil drilling fields from the Dutch era. Supporting facilities for the development of Lapang Museum includes plazas, adventure zones, viewing posts, a culinary area, prayer rooms, lavatory, landfills, and gazebo.', '2019-09-09 02:42:11', '2019-09-09 02:42:11'),
