(176, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 80, 'en', 'Tritip Cave, which is located in Ujungwatu Village, Donorejo Sub-district, Jepara Regency, is a tourist object on hillsides near other potential tourist objects that can be developed. It is named Tritip Cave because there is a cave between rock slits with uneven texture which is called Tritip in Javanese. Local community believes this cave has a place to refuge because there are some ship pieces owned by Mbah Joyo Kusumo. Activities that can be done when tourists come to Tritip Goa are camping, tracking around the hill, or hiking to the top of the hill to see the wondrous sea and hills scenery around the area. Other potential tourist attractions around Tritip Cave include natural agricultural land, hill track, photo spots, and rest area with mountains, rice fields, trees, and beaches as backgrounds. Furthermore, there is also a mini café, viewing points, tree house, swings, sunset and sunrise sceneries, flying fox and paragliding, off-road track, and open space which can be utilized as performance or exhibition spot.', '2019-09-09 02:45:48', '2019-09-09 02:45:48'),
