(185, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 82, 'en', 'Located in Bulu Village, Jepara Sub-District, Central Java Province with an area of 19,2 Ha. Panjang Island is located 2 km from Kartini Beach of Jepara and 80 km from Karimunjawa Islands. Panjang Island has the beauty of white sand beaches surrounded by clear shallow seas and coral reefs. In the central part of Panjang Island lies a tropical forest with tall trees among shrubs and bushes as places for seabirds to breed. The facilities that are offered around the tomb consists of a mushala (small prayer room), a place for ablution (wudhu), toilet, and there is also barokah water from a well nearby and can be consumed by visitors. Visitors who want to do marine tourism will be charged IDR 3,000.00 per person and can immediately enjoy the beach which has relatively small waves. Other sports provided in Panjang Island are snorkeling, canoeing, and bicycle rental to explore the island. In addition, most visitors who want to spend the night in Panjang Island can do camping in camping ground area provided on the beach.', '2019-09-09 02:59:44', '2019-09-09 02:59:44'),
