(203, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 84, 'en', 'Boja Swimming Pool is located in Kaliwungu Boja Street No. 27, Sapen, Boja, Kendal Regency, Central Java and managed by Kendal Regency government. There are two pools here, namely “prestasi” swimming pool and “rekreasi” swimming pool. With the depth of ±2 meters, the length of 50 meters, and the width of 20 meters, “prestasi” swimming pool is often used for holding swimming competitions. The number of domestic tourists visiting Boja Swimming Pool in 2017 was 46,612 people and it was the highest total of visitors compared to other water attractions in the region. As for facilities, this place has water slides, spilled giant bucket, three in one, and a water fountain with bursts with the height of 5 meters. In addition, there are also facilities such as changing rooms, gazebo, praying room (mushola), and food stalls.', '2019-09-09 03:06:17', '2019-09-09 03:06:17'),
