(212, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 85, 'en', 'This tourism spot has 661,545 visitors until 2017 and is still the leading tourism attraction in Kudus Regency. Attractions that are offered here are religious tourism and nature tourism. Tourists who come here are expected not only to do pilgrimage to Sunan Muria’s tomb, but also do sports, have a relaxing time, or spend a night in this place to enjoy the scenery and coolness of Muria highlands. Spending 30,000.00 IDR for entrance ticket, Visitors are also offered with sports facilities, outbond, food and beverages stalls. Not only developing religious sites which are filled with interesting facilities, Colo has also a well supporting environment in terms of its geographical, water, and air condition. Although it is located in highland, Colo has an accessible roads because it can be passed by motorcycles, cars, and even buses.', '2019-09-09 03:09:29', '2019-09-09 03:09:29'),
