(221, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 86, 'en', 'Banyutowo Fishing Port has an important meaning for fishing communities in Pati Regency, especially in wild fisheries activities and other fisheries works. The potential of fisheries production from the Java Sea makes the condition of wild fisheries in Banyutowo Fishing Port reach 1,061,027 kg and it is also supported by a fleet of 219 units, consisting of 21 motor boats and 198 units of outboard motors. The number of fishermen in Banyutowo Fishing Port reach 908 people that consist of 159 skippers and 749 pandega (employees on a fishing vessel). With an area of 2 Ha, this fishing port can be the center of various fisheries activities, namely for fish auction sites, fisheries management industries, cold storage, workshops, offices, banks, and shops. The development of Banyutowo Fishing Port is expected further can increase local economic development to provide employment opportunities along with be able to improve the community condition by utilizing existing resources.', '2019-09-09 03:15:38', '2019-09-09 03:15:38'),
(222, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 86, 'en', 'The development of Banyutowo fishing port includes building 3 docks, 2 breakwaters, workshops, harbor nets, small department store and village cooperative unit (koperasi unit desa), fishing shelters, cold storage, ice, processing, and packing factories, stalls, generators and shops, as well as docking.', '2019-09-09 03:15:38', '2019-09-09 03:15:38'),
(223, 'proyeks', 'eksisting', 86, 'en', '-	In a form of land with an area of 2 Ha. The existing condition of Basis Landing of Fish (PPI) Banyutowo master plan are already starting built infrastructure, such as road access from concrete rabates, fish market building, Fishrmen Solar Packet Dealer building, and drainage in the fish market area. Fishermen still conduct auction in the old fish market area because the new fish market has not been able to operate. -	Road access to the location', '2019-09-09 03:15:38', '2019-09-09 03:15:38'),
