(302, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 97, 'en', 'Keburuhan Beach is located in Keburuhan Village, Ngombol Sub-district, Purworejo Regency. Access to the beach can be passed by two-wheeled vehicles as well as four-wheeled vehicles. But for four-wheeled vehicles, it can’t get close to the beach because visitors have to pass a wooden bridge which is only 2 m wide. Its location close to Kulon Progo Sub-district where there is a construction of the New Yogyakarta International Airport and is expected to be an opportunity to increase visitors who come to Keburuhan Beach. The development of Keburuhan Beach includes construction of a water park, lodging facilities and infrastructures, worship place, food stalls, mangrove planting, dock establishment in the south river, creating Keburuhan Beach landmark, and improving the quality of the hall area.', '2019-09-09 04:03:32', '2019-09-09 04:32:47'),
(303, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 97, 'en', '1.	Welcome zone as the main entrance area that includes:  - Development of area gate and repair of ticket counters  - Vegetation arrangement on the side of road in the form of reffering trees along entrance road to Keburuhan Village  - Signage addition in the form of information board of the tourism site and some street lighting  2.	Development zone that is divided into: - Waterpark zone  - Lodging and resort zone, acade/souvenir arena  3.	Conservation zone (mangrove conservation area)  4.	Buffer zone', '2019-09-09 04:03:32', '2019-09-09 04:32:47'),
(304, 'proyeks', 'eksisting', 97, 'en', 'Access to the beach is very convenient, can be accessed by 2-wheels and 4-wheels transportation. But 4-wheels transportation can\'t get exactly to the beach because before we reach the beach, we have to pass a wood bridge that has a wide only of 2 m. The quality of accessibility to Keburuhan Beach is relatively poor, with roads condition that are still hollow and rocky, especially the Daendels Road that leads to the coastal area', '2019-09-09 04:03:32', '2019-09-09 04:32:47'),
(305, 'proyeks', 'status_kepemilikan', 97, 'en', 'Purworejo Regency Government', '2019-09-09 04:03:32', '2019-09-09 04:32:47'),
