(320, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 98, 'en', 'The development of Bagelen Drinking Water Supply System is planned to utilize raw water from Bogowonto River, specifically in Kedung Ponggoh which is located in Dadirejo Village, Bagelen Sub-district. Bogowonto River was chosen because according to the analysis result from Cooperation Institute of Engineering Faculty in Gadjah Mada University, the potential of water that can be utilized inn Bogowonto River downstream is 58 liters per second. This development is expected to increase the coverage of drinking water supply in Purwodadi Sub-district, especially Bagelen Sub-district which consists of five villages and Purwodadi Sub-district which consists of 12 villages. In addition, it is also expected that Bagelen Drinking Water Supply System can capture the opportunity as the drinking water provider for New Yogyakarta International Airport area because the distance is only 5 km from the airport.', '2019-09-09 04:13:48', '2019-09-09 04:13:48'),
