(391, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 105, 'en', 'Clapar Agritourism Area covers an area of 8 ha and is located in Clapar Village, Subah Sub-district, Batang Regency, passed by the National North Coast Road (Pantura). This tourism site has elongated land and is dominated by plantation area with various plant varieties, such as durian, mangosteen, banana, orange, mango, and other types of fruit. As for supporting facilities in Clapar Agritourism Area, the management provides a laboratory, hydroponic greenhouse, showroom, bathroom, and other facilities. The further development of this agritourism area will include adjustment to the land that has been conceptualized, rest area facilities, other agritourism zones such as production site of superior plants nursery, orange garden, cafés, souvenir shop, as well as screen house for nursery and fertilizer production. In addition, game rides namely flying fox, labyrinth park, slides, educational tourism, camping ground, and playground will also be added to the further development of Clapar Agritourism Area. ', '2019-09-09 06:45:34', '2019-09-09 06:45:34'),
(392, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 105, 'en', 'Clapar Agro-tourism Development includes the construction of green houses, restaurants, lobbies, plazas, glamping ground, amphitheater, elevated walkways, labyrinth games, flying fox, and water games.', '2019-09-09 06:45:34', '2019-09-09 06:45:34'),
(393, 'proyeks', 'eksisting', 105, 'en', 'Plantation conditions are generally attractive but rarely visited by visitors because of its public facilities, such as main road or entrance that does not reflect a tourist destinaton. Its location on a busy street, namely Pantura Lane, which should be a magnet in itself but it is less of concern and reducing interest for visiting the area.', '2019-09-09 06:45:34', '2019-09-09 06:45:34'),
