(400, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 106, 'en', 'Cemara Island is known with its bird islands, beaches, culinary, camping ground, sunset scenery, and also selfie spots. Other facilities in this island are solar power plants, artesian wells, decent sanitation, and engine boats for mobility. Visitors can also rent banana boats and ATVs or just spend a day catching a fish in some fishing spots. The number of Cemara Island visitors in 2018 reached 72,873 people because this place is always crowded during Eid al Fitr holidays as well as New Year holidays. Entrance ticket fee for weekdays and weekends is IDR 15,000.00 per person, exclude IDR 5,000.00 for car parking fee and IDR 2.000,00 for motorcycle parking fee. The development of Cemara Island includes the construction of two docks, entrance gate, bridge, tracking track, 2 gazebos, prayer rooms, bathrooms, viewing post, and an arena for banana boats, ATVs, watercrafts, and boats. In addition, there are also other facilities that will be created, namely fishing cages, playground for kids, fish ponds, parking lot, health post, management office, canteen, park, souvenir kiosk, and promotional car.', '2019-09-09 07:08:01', '2019-09-09 07:08:01'),
(401, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 106, 'en', 'Construction of 2 docks, a gate, kiosk, a management office, water rides such as banana boats, jet skis, ATVs, children\'s games, fishing cages, and fish ponds.', '2019-09-09 07:08:01', '2019-09-09 07:08:01'),
