(445, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 111, 'en', 'Tegal Regency has a nature tourism star, namely Cantel Waterfall (Curug) that has preserved flora and fauna as well as waterfall which is the main attraction of this tourism site. In an area of 20 ha, Cantel Waterfall also has moist soil for farming and horticulture, pine forests, Sigedong rural area, views of the hilly area and green scenery of the leaves among cold air. This tourism area location is in Kalipedes Hamlet, Segendong Village, Bumijawa Sub-district, Tegal Regency which is on the border of Tegal Regency and Brebes Regency, precisely on the edge of Kalipedes main road. In general, Cantel waterfall has a tropical climate, but the area is cooler because of its location around mountainside. Visitors who come will only be charged an entrance fee of IDR 5,000.00 per person.', '2019-09-09 07:42:06', '2019-09-09 07:42:06'),
(446, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 111, 'en', 'Cantel Waterfall Development will include building cottages, suspension bridge, swimming pool, and integrated tourist building.', '2019-09-09 07:42:06', '2019-09-09 07:42:06'),
