(454, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 112, 'en', 'One of the plans in developing coastal areas in Pemalang Regency is by establishing fisheries infrastructures and facilities. This is because in 2017, there were ±14,945 people working as fishermen, with 10,406 of them having status as pandega (employee on a fishing vessel). Observed from the growth of fishing boats that continue to increase every year, the establishment of a dock will be a suitable option to choose. The selected location for this dock is Asemdoyong Public Fish Market (TPI). Asemdoyong Public Fish Market was chosen because it is the second biggest wharf and fish market, which reached 7,639 tons. Production tools owned by the fishermen are generally outboard motors with a total of 1,582 units and 88 motorboats. With these amounts above, it is necessary to build a dock in Asemdoyong Public Fish Market that can be utilized by local fishermen together to improve the regional economy.', '2019-09-09 07:45:09', '2019-09-09 07:45:09'),
