(463, 'proyeks', 'latar_belakang', 113, 'en', 'Pekalongan Mangrove Park is the new name of Mangrove Information Center (PIM). This area is a tourist attraction that physically has a pretty good nature to be developed and has a potential educational purpose. The lack of facilities provided makes Pekalongan Mangrove Park only has few visitors than other tourist attractions because the activities that can be done here do not require much time. Activities that can be chosen by visitors are reading books, seeing a boat miniature, taking pictures, taking a rest, strolling around, watching the scenery from the height, and exploring mangrove forest. The plan for developing Pekalongan Mangrove Park is to repair entrance gate, tourist information center, mangrove information center, jogging track, and gazebo. As for the addition of facilities consists of parking areas, seafood culinary, art and culture amphitheater, and boat tour. The repaired and added facilities will be supporting each other for the activities of tourists visiting Pekalongan Mangrove Park.', '2019-09-09 07:48:02', '2019-09-09 07:48:02'),
(464, 'proyeks', 'lingkup_pekerjaan', 113, 'en', 'Repairment and improvement of the existing infrastructure in order to restore the original concept of the tourism site as an educational tourism area. Facilities improvement include on entrance gate, tourist information center, jogging track, and gazebo. While for additional facilities, there will be construction for parking area, seafood culinary, art and culture amphitheater, as well as tourist boat', '2019-09-09 07:48:02', '2019-09-09 07:48:02'),
(465, 'proyeks', 'eksisting', 113, 'en', 'The facilities built are few. Although the development has not yet completed but the existing facilities are damaged. Most of the facilities are abandoned so some of them are broken. The existing attraction potential in this tourism site is not utilized optimally, especially mangrove jogging track and tourist boat so it can attract visitors to come', '2019-09-09 07:48:02', '2019-09-09 07:48:02'),
