(965, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 83, 'en', 'Tegal City is one of the cities in Central Java Province that is located on Pantura lane, between Jakarta City and Semarang City, and on the south lane from Purwokerto City-Yogyakarta City route. This city has an area of 39.68 km2 and consists of four sub-districts and 27 urban sub-districts. Has a distance of 162 km from Semarang City, this city has a very adequate infrastructure, namely paved roads, State Electricity Company (PLN) networks, Telkom networks, Regional Water Company (PDAM), postal clearing, train station, bus terminal, commercial port, banking, hospital health unit/Community Health Center (Puskesmas), educational institutions, and universities. Tegal City Government nowadays is promoting a spirit to maintain local culture that has a red line with the concept of Tegal Yekan Park integrated area which portrays a complete tourism of art, culture, excellence regional products, and culinary.', '2019-09-15 11:16:58', '2019-09-15 11:16:58'),
(966, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 82, 'en', 'Purbalingga Regency is located in a basin between mountain chain and is bordered by Pemalang Regency in north, Banjarnegara Regency in east and south, as well as Banyumas Regency in west. It is acknowledged by its industry of human hairs for creating fake eyelashes, wigs, buns, and additional fake hairs. These days this regency is encouraging the development of its natural tourism sector in the hope that it will give positive impact to the local community economic condition as well as introduce the diversity of nature, history, and culture in Purbalingga Regency.', '2019-09-15 11:18:33', '2019-09-15 11:18:33'),
(967, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 81, 'en', 'Pemalang Regency is one of the regencies in Central Java Province that is divided into 14 sub-districts, 11 urban sub-districts, and 211 villages. The northern part of this regency is lowlands in the form of coastal area with the height of 1-5 m above sea level. The central part is fertile lowlands with a height of 6-15 m above sea level, whereas the southern part consists of highlands in the form of fertile mountains with the height of 16-925 m above sea level. This regency is one of the regencies in Central Java Province which has a marine area with a coastline of ±35 km. This condition makes Pemalang regency has a huge potential in marine fisheries to support the lives of coastal communities.', '2019-09-15 11:19:58', '2019-09-15 11:19:58'),
(968, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 80, 'en', 'Pekalongan Regency with an area of 836,13 km2 consists of 285 urban sub-districts; 60 villages are located in the highlands and 225 villages are located in the lowlands. The northern part of Pekalongan Regency borders Java Sea and Pekalongan City. In the east, it is bordered with Batang Regency and Pekalongan City, Banjarnegara Regency and Purbalingga Regency in the south, and Pemalang Regency in the west. The economic growth of Pekalongan Regency in 2017 was 5.16% and one of the sectors that experienced accelerated growth was the accommodation sector which also supported other sectors. Accelerated growth in this sector indicates that this sector has a potential to be developed.', '2019-09-15 11:29:21', '2019-09-15 11:29:21'),
(969, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 79, 'en', 'ekalongan City is one of autonomous regions in Central Java Province and has a strategic location because it is located along the northern coast of the Java Sea and is passed by a main road connecting the western and eastern part of Java Island. The total area of Pekalongan City is 4,525Ha and consists of 4 sub-districts and 27 urban sub-districts. Access to this city can be done from different regions with the availability of existing roads and the further road development plans increase the accessibility to the city. Various types of transportation also create an opportunity for Pekalongan City to be explored. Observed from its location along the northern part of the Java Sea, Pekalongan City has a nature tourism that is related to the coast and also Mangrove Information Center (PIM)', '2019-09-15 11:34:17', '2019-09-15 11:34:17'),
(970, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 78, 'en', 'The majority of Brebes Regency population speaks Javanese language but it has a distinctive character from common Javanese and usually called as Brebes Javanese language. Besides Javanese, a part of Brebes residents use Sundanese language where they commonly live in Salem Sub-district, Banjarhajo Sub-district, and Bantarkawung Sub-district, also some villages in Losari Sub-district, Tanjung Sub-district, Kersana Sub-district, Ketanggungan Sub-district, and Larang Sub-district. Brebes Regency is divided into three areas, which are mountains, hills, and beaches. This regency has 52 tourism spots, and one of them is Cemara Island in Sawojajar Village, Wanasari Sub-district, Brebes Regency.', '2019-09-15 11:36:00', '2019-09-15 11:36:00'),
(971, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 77, 'en', 'Batang Regency has an area of 78,864.16 Hectare that is bordered by the Java Sea in the north, Kendal Regency in the east, Wonosobo Regency and Banjarnegara Regency in the south, as well as Pekalongan City and Regency in the west. The area of this regency is divided into three regions, namely beach, lowland, and mountainous area. The mountain area has high potential to establish regional development with characteristics of agro-industry, agribusiness, and agritourism. The south area of Batang Regency consists of mountainous regions that can be developed as nature tourism by utilizing existing resources.', '2019-09-15 11:37:21', '2019-09-15 11:37:21'),
(972, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 76, 'en', 'n an area of 132,758 Ha, Banyumas Regency consists of 27 sub-districts and 331 villages/sub-districts. It borders Tegal Regency and Pemalang Regency in the north; Purbalingga Regency, Banjarnegara Regency, and Kebumen Regency in the east; Cilacap Regency and Brebes Regency in the west; and Cilacap Regency in the south. The economic growth of Banyumas Regency is satisfactory, starting from the agricultural sector and now is shifting to trade and industrial sector, even rapidly expanding in tourism sector. These days Kabupaten Banyumas tourism is well known with Baturaden as its star. Nevertheless, Banyumas Regency Government is planning to establish Kota Baru area and the construction of a tower as the next icon', '2019-09-15 11:38:39', '2019-09-15 11:38:39'),
(973, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 75, 'en', 'Banjarnegara Regency has an area of 106,970.977 Ha with 20 sub-districts, 266 villages, and 12 urban sub-districts in it. The northern part of Banjarnegara is bordered by Batang Regency and Pekalongan Regency; in the south, it borders Kebumen Regency; Purbalingga Regency is adjacent with this regency; and also Wonosobo Regency is bordered with this regency in the east. The distance of Banjarnegara Regency to Semarang Regency can be reached for 3.5 hours by land. This regency is also close to the famous Dieng Plateau that is known because of its coolness and is a perfect choice to spend holiday. One of the potential tourism sites to be developed is Merdada Lake in the Dieng', '2019-09-15 11:39:50', '2019-09-15 11:39:50'),
(974, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 74, 'en', 'Cilacap Regency occupies an area of 225,362 ha and is bordered by Kuningan Regency, Brebes Regency, and Banyumas Regency in the north; Indonesia Ocean in the south; Kebumen Regency in the east; together with Ciamis Regency and Banjar City of West Java Province in the west. This regency is divided into 24 sub-districts, 269 villages, and 15 urban sub-districts. Cilacap Regency is recognized as one of the center of fisheries sector in Indonesia because Cilacap has an extensive coastal area that stretches from Patimuran Sub-district in the west to Nusawungu Sub-district in the east, with a coastline of 105 km. Along with the fisheries area, this regency also has a great potential in the farming sector to be developed.', '2019-09-15 11:42:00', '2019-09-15 11:42:00'),
(975, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 73, 'en', 'Wonogiri Regency consists of 25 sub-districts, 43 urban sub-districts, and 251 villages. It is borders Karanganyar Regency and Sukoharjo Regency in the north; South Coast in the south; Mount Kidul in the west; and the East Java Province in the east. This regency is known with its tiwul rice and various types of food, namely cashew nuts and chips. This regency has numerous destinations that can be visited, such as spiritual tourism, adventure, beach tourism, nature tourism, and others. One of the tourism spots that will be developed is Conto Village in Bulukerto Sub-district, Wonogiri Regency or specifically on the south side of Lawu Mountain hillside.', '2019-09-15 11:44:37', '2019-09-15 11:44:37'),
(976, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 72, 'en', 'Sukoharjo Regency is a buffer zone for the Solo City and the new Solo City as a satellite city that coincides with Surakarta City and is strategically located at the intersection of Semarang, Yogyakarta, Solo, and Surabaya. Its location in the golden triangle of Yogyakarta-Solo-Semarang  makes the development of Sukoharjo Regency in various sectors increase rapidly,such as improvements in the industrial sector, trading, agriculture, education, culture, public facilities, transportation, banking, and tourism. One of the tourism developments that is executed by Sukohajo Regency is the development of tourism village. Sukoharjo Regency has Kenep Sub-district with its various tourism potentials provided. This urban sub-district will be developed as Kenep Creative Tourist Village.', '2019-09-15 11:46:26', '2019-09-15 11:46:26'),
(977, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 71, 'en', 'Sragen Regency has an area of 94,155 ha and is divided into 20 sub-districts, 8 urban sub-districts, and 200 villages. The distance of Sragen Regency to Semarang City is ±115 km by land. In addition, access to this regency can be reached by sea and air. The closest ports from Sragen Regency are Tanjung Emas Port in Semarang which is 121 km away and Tanjung Perak Port in Surabaya which is 238 km away. For the air route, there are several airports closest to Sragen Regency, namely Adi Sumarmo Airport in Solo with a distance of 40 km, Adisutjipto Airport in Yogyakarta which is 85 km away, and Juanda Airport in Surabaya that has a distance of 233 km from the regency. This regency also has Kartika Swimming Pool which is always filled with visitors both on weekdays and weekends. The tourists come from all ages, ranging from children, adolescents and adults.', '2019-09-15 11:48:42', '2019-09-15 11:48:42'),
(978, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 70, 'en', 'Geographically, Purworejo Regency is an area located on the Indian Ocean coast, the southern part of Java Island. This regency is one of the developing regions and is supported by the development plan, including the tourism sector. One of the efforts to develop the tourism that will be done is by establishing Keburuhan Beach. Keburuhan Beach is chosen because it is considered to have future potential according to its location which is near to Kulon Progo Sub-district which is currently constructing the New Yogyakarta International Airport. This condition is expected to provide an opportunity for Keburuhan Beach in the future. In addition, this airport presence can also give a potential to Tirta Perwitasari Regional Water Company (PDAM) of Purworejo Regency in order to increase the demand of drinking water demand.', '2019-09-15 11:50:26', '2019-09-15 11:50:26'),
(979, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 69, 'en', 'Magelang Regency has a highly strategic location in the Central Java Province because it is located on the intersection of economy and tourism between Semarang-Magelang-Yogyakarta and Purworejo-Temanggung. The area of Magelang Regency is 1,102.93 or ±3.34% of Central Java Province area and is divided into 21 sub-districts. The distance of Magelang Regency and Semarang City is 9.54 km and it can be reached by land. This regency has tourism designation areas that are relatively vast and are divided into cultural tourism, nature tourism, and man-made tourism. This gives a valuable opportunity if there is proper lodging facilities which can also support tourism activities in Magelang Regency.', '2019-09-15 11:52:14', '2019-09-15 11:52:14'),
(980, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 68, 'en', 'Located in the center of Java Island makes Magelang City has a natural geographic attraction because it is placed on the intersection of economic, transportation, and tourism between Sema-rang-Magelang-Yogyakarta and Purwore-jo-Temanggung. In an area of 18.53 km2, this city is known as the City of Million Flowers which has a philosophy as Tuin van Java (City of Gardens/Park in Java). Magelang City also has the former Magelang Theater building that has adequately strate-gic location and is valuable to be developed so it can give positive impact to the city development.', '2019-09-15 11:53:12', '2019-09-15 11:53:12'),
(981, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 67, 'en', 'Klaten Regency was originally a former of self-governing Surakarta region which had long been known for its land fertility. This regency is located among Merapi Mount and Seribu Mountains with a height of 75-160 above sea level. Klaten Regency has various potentials, namely agriculture sector, plantation sector, fisheries sector, mining sector, forestry sector, micro-and-small-scale industry, as well as tourist village potential. One of the tourist village potentials in Klaten Regency is nature tourism area in Kratitan Village that has floating shops which serve various kinds of processed freshwater fish.', '2019-09-15 11:54:11', '2019-09-15 11:54:11'),
(982, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 66, 'en', 'The name of Kebumen is said to have originated from the word “kabumian” which means “as the resident place of Kyai Bumi”. Mostly, Kebumen Regency inhabitants use Javanese language as their daily language. But if we look at the accent, the language spoken by the Kebumen Regency people is divided into several accents. This regency is the third biggest coconut producer region in Java Island. This condition can be an opportunity to be utilized for processing coconuts into palm sugar, seeing the number of people consuming palm sugar because of its good health effects.', '2019-09-15 11:55:26', '2019-09-15 11:55:26'),
(983, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 65, 'en', 'Karanganyar Regency has an area of 77,378,637 ha and divided into 165 villages, 15 urban sub-districts, and 17 sub-districts. Fulfilling Sapta Pesona values which are safe, neat, clean, cool, beautiful, friendly, and memories make Karanganyar Regency visited by many tourists. One of Karanganyar Regency’s beauties is Sukuh Temple which is a 15th Hindu temple from King Brawijaya V. Sukuh Temple is located in the hills of Barjo Village, Ngargoyoso Sub-District, Karanganyar and precisely 23 km from Karanganyar City. There are two main areas of Sukuh Temple, which are Kemuning Park and Gondang Reservoir Park, which have a role as the backbone of Sukuh Temple and have its own attraction for tourists.', '2019-09-15 11:57:56', '2019-09-15 11:57:56'),
(984, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 55, 'en', 'Grobogan Regency with an area of 1,975.85 km2 is the second widest regency in Central Java Province and consists of 19 sub-districts, 273 villages, and 7 urban sub-districts. The distance between Grobogan Regency capital city and Semarang City is 64 km. Access to Grobogan Regency can be reached by using ground transportations through Solo, Semarang, Demak, Pati, Kudus, Boyolali, Blora, Sragen, and Ngawi. This regency has contributed in agriculture sector through three main food commodities, namely rice, corn, and soybeans. One of the things that supports the economy of Grobogan Regency is the agricultural sector by having around 83.94% of the land used for agricultural activities. Besides agriculture, another thing that strengthen the economic condition is tourism development by utilizing some areas in Grobogan Regency as tourist villages. This was done to prompt socio-economic development of the surrounding community while supporting the development of tourism villages.', '2019-09-15 12:01:58', '2019-09-15 12:01:58'),
(985, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 54, 'en', 'Demak Regency is a region which is located next to Semarang City with an area of 89,743 Ha and consists of 14 sub-districts, 241 villages, and 6 urban villages. The location is adequately strategic as a supporting area in economic sector of Central Java because it is on the crowded North Coast Road (Pantai Utara Jawa) traffic lane. Demak Regency region consists of lowlands, beaches, and hills. Water sources in this region come from rivers, seas, and beaches. Seas and beaches in Demak Regency have a valuable potential for development in fishery, aquaculture, and tourism. It is proved that some of sub-districts in Demak Regency have been starting to utilize seas and beaches in fishery sector and its beautiful scenery for tourism.', '2019-09-15 12:03:45', '2019-09-15 12:03:45'),
(986, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 64, 'en', 'With an area of 1,015.10 km2, Boyolali Regency is strategic location because it has become the traffic flow between big cities, such as Yogyakarta, Semarang, and Surakarta. The distance of Boyolali Regency from Semarang City is 80.9 km and can be reached for 2 hours by land. The economic growth of Boyolali Regency increase every year and this happens because each sector contributes well. One of the biggest contributors in Boyolali Regency economic structure is the industrial sector that has grown in recent years. Industrial development in this regency is quite rapid, especially in urban suburbs areas.', '2019-09-15 12:05:15', '2019-09-15 12:05:15'),
(987, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 63, 'en', 'Located at an altitude of 250-2,250 meters above sea level, making Wonosobo Regency in a mountainous region with a cool microclimate and has air temperature between 14.3o-26.5oC. Soil material formed in Wonosobo Regency is the result of volcanic processes from Mount Sumbing, Mount Sindoro, and Dieng Mountains, so it has an effect on high soil fertility. The beautiful nature in Wonosobo Regency has a special attraction for the tourism sector. Besides its nature beauty, Wonosobo Regency also has natural products which are also tourist destinations, one of them is hot springs. The famous hot spring in Wonosobo Regency is Kalianget Hot Spring which is located in Kalianget Village and is quite accessible.', '2019-09-15 12:06:41', '2019-09-15 12:06:41'),
(988, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 62, 'en', 'Temanggung Regency has an area of 87,065 Ha and is located in the center of economic activities in some Central Java and Special Region of Yogyakarta cities, which are Semarang City, Yogyakarta City, and Purwokerto City. The economic growth rate of Temanggung Regency in 2017 is indeed lower compared to other cities in Central Java Province and nationally, but the government has created plans to improve this issue, one of them is developing tourism sector in Temanggung Regency.  Tourism development implemented is community-based tourism which has more opportunities to develop small-scale tourism objects and attractions. This community-based tourism will involve local residents in its development, and one of them has been started in Kledung Sub-district.', '2019-09-15 12:08:47', '2019-09-15 12:08:47'),
(989, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 61, 'en', 'Surakarta City with an area of 44.04 km2 is divided into 5 sub-districts and 54 urban sub-districts. The distance from Semarang City is ±105 km and can be reached through highways with for around an hour and 40 minutes. This city has developed plentiful creative industries, including batik, handicraft, food, furniture, bird cages, shuttlecocks, patchwork, and others. The growing number of creative industries also encourages various kind of events to be held every year and makes Surakarta City as the city of MICE (meetings, incentives, conventions, exhibitions). This can be potential for Surakarta City if it has a convention-exhibition hall which can be used to hold various kinds of local, national, and', '2019-09-15 12:10:32', '2019-09-15 12:10:32'),
(990, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 60, 'en', 'Semarang City is the capital of Central Java Province and it has an area of 373.70 km2. It consists of 16 sub-district and 177 urban sub-districts with total population of 1,815,729 inhabitants. Semarang City has a large number of infrastructures, from an airport, harbors, train stations, highways, and in-land transportation terminals. Other than that, this city has other facilities, such as education facilities, banks, health institutions, golf fields, tourist attractions, hotels, and industrial area as well. Semarang is irrefut-ably an area full of potential and profitable in economic, social, culture, and other aspects. Being the center of trade and services, Sema-rang has an opportunity to organize MICE (meetings, incentives, conferences, exhibi-tions) activities. Evidently in 2014, there were 3,958,115 tourists visiting this city, including MICE business trips related.', '2019-09-15 12:12:32', '2019-09-15 12:12:32'),
(991, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 59, 'en', 'Based on an inscription that is found in Plumpungan Hamlet, Kauman Kidul Village, Sidorejo Sub-district, Salatiga City has existed since 750 AD and at that time, Salatiga was an area within a certain kingdom. Nowadays Salatiga City is located in the middle of Semarang Regency with four sub-districts and 23 urban sub-districts. In 2012, the area of Salatiga City was recorded at 56.781 km2. This city is currently planning for industrial area development that can be the center of industrial activities and as a part of long-term economic development. Besides, Salatiga City is also expecting to establish a souvenir center that can contribute to the long-term economic development as well.', '2019-09-15 12:13:52', '2019-09-15 12:13:52'),
(992, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 58, 'en', 'Kudus Regency is found by Sunan Kudus Raden Ja’far Shodiq on Ramadan 1, 956, in the Hijri calendar or September 23, 1549, in the Gregorian calendar. Kudus, which comes from “Al-Quds” in Arabic and means “holy”, was formally established on July 6, 1990. Kudus Regency has an economic growth that are dominated by trading, industry, construction, finance, transportation, warehousing, communication, and other service sectors. The economic growth of Kudus Regency keeps progressing without neglecting its religious matters. It is proved by the constant arrival of visitors to do pilgrimage to Sunan Muria’s tomb. It is done to show Kudus Regency which is not only modern, smart, and prosperous, but also maintains its religious value that is carried in its name.', '2019-09-15 12:15:19', '2019-09-15 12:15:19'),
(993, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 56, 'en', 'Kendal Regency has an area of 1,002.23 km2, which is divided into 3 regions which are mountains and hills, lowlands, as well as beaches. The area of Kendal Regency includes lowlands area with an altitude between 0-15 meters above sea level and consist of 12 sub-districts. In addition, the hilly areas to mountains have an altitude of 100-641 meters above sea level and consist of 8 sub-districts. This regency offers various types of tourism attractions that are not only used for leisure purposes, but also as places for races. One of tourism spots that is frequently used for races is a swimming pool that is managed by regional government of Kendal Regency. Besides the swimming pool, the beauty of its waterfall is quite a popular option for water tourism activity in Kendal Regency.', '2019-09-15 12:16:17', '2019-09-15 12:16:17'),
(994, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 53, 'en', 'Known for the slogan “Blora Mustika”, Blora Regency is located in the easternmost part of Central Java Province together with Rembang Regency. The distance of Blora Regency to Semarang City is 127 km. This region has an area of 182,058,797 Ha which consist of paddy fields and non-paddy fields. Blora Regency is at 40 to 500 meters above sea level with the highest rainfall in Japah Sub-district, which is 165 days. Blora Regency has 10 sub-districts that have become industrial area with each various outcome. One of those is Tunjungan Sub-district which has a reservoir and become one of the most visited places by tourists in 2017, with 124,000 visitors.', '2019-09-15 12:19:53', '2019-09-15 12:19:53'),
(995, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 51, 'en', 'Semarang Regency consists of 19 sub-districts, 108 villages, and 27 urban sub-districts with Ungaran as its regency capital city. Semarang Regency borders Semarang City, Boyolali Regency, Kendal Regency, and Salatiga City. This regency is a very strategic area because it is located between the triangular connecting lines of the regional development centers, namely Semarang, Solo, and Yogyakarta. There are 125 water springs spread through Semarang Regency and it makes this regency has adequate surface and ground water sourc-es. Most of the Semarang Regency area is hilly and has reliefs of volcanic mountain areas and plains in the middle. The hilly and mountain-ous conditions makes Semarang Regency covered in cool air with beautiful panoramas and it can be a good potential in its nature tourism.', '2019-09-15 12:22:18', '2019-09-15 12:22:18'),
(996, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 50, 'en', 'Rembang Regency is a region that directly borders East Java Province, making this region the east gate of Central Java Province. The distance of the center of Rembang City to Semarang City is 123 km. This regency has some decent infrastructures, namely Pantura lane and in-development Rembang Port in Sluke Sub-District in the form of Sluke Terminal as an entrance gate for sea vehicles. The north part of Rembang Regency is bordered by Rembang Bay and it has a coastline with ±62 km which has a great marine potential. This efficacy is supported by the availability of 10 fish auction centers (TPI) in the sub-district which is located in Pantura Lane. In addition, there are also a commercial port and 3 fishing ports. These opportunities can make many people around this place have had their own vessels since their profession is fishermen.', '2019-09-15 12:23:25', '2019-09-15 12:23:25'),
(997, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 49, 'en', 'Pati Regency, which has 21 sub-districts with 401 villages and 5 urban sub-districts, is a regency that is 75 km from Semarang City. This regency is located on the Northern Coast Lane (Pantura). Furthermore the north and east part of this regency borders Java Sea. Its border with Java Sea makes Pati Regency rich in its fisheries sector. This sector is also one of the biggest economic supports for Pati Regency. This regency has contributed significantly in fisheries both in regional and national levels. One of the ports with wild fishery products that is quite large and has the potential to be developed more complex and integrated is Banyutowo Fishing Port', '2019-09-15 12:24:05', '2019-09-15 12:24:05'),
(998, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 48, 'en', 'Jepara Regency is the northernmost region in the Central Java Province, which has a tropical climate with two seasons, namely rain and dry seasons. Located on the east part of Pantura Street of Central Java, the west and north area of Jepara Regency are separated by sea while the east area is mountainous. With an area of 1,004,132 km2, Jepara Regency consists of 16 districts, 11 sub-districts, and 184 villages. Its location can be accessed through two ways, which are land and sea lanes. Particularly through sea route, this regency can be reached through Tanjung Emas Port in Semarang and Kartini Beach in Jepara. Even though it is not traversed by Pantura Road (North Coast Road), Jepara Regency still has a strategic potential when it is referred from its sea geographical location with a coastline of ±82 km and highly capable for tourism development. Aside of marine tourism development, Jepara Regency also has hills area which is potential for farming and forestry development.', '2019-09-15 12:25:09', '2019-09-15 12:25:09'),
(999, 'profil_kabupatens', 'profil', 85, 'en', 'Tegal Regency', '2019-09-16 05:01:35', '2019-09-16 05:01:35'),
(1000, 'profil_kabupatens', 'desc_profil', 85, 'en', 'Tegal Regency has an area of 87,879 Ha and is divided into 18 sub-districts, 281 villages, and six urban sub-districts. The northern part of this region is bordered by Tegal City and Java Sea, in the south is bordered by Brebes Regency and Banyumas Regency, the west part is bordered by Brebes Regency, and in the east part is bordered by Pemalang Regency. The distance of Tegal Regency to Semarang City is 164.5 km and can be reached by land. This regency has a potential in nature tourism where flora and fauna are still very well maintained and the panorama of waterfalls. It also has plans to develop Tegal industrial area in order to drive its economy and provide support for all productive resources owned.', '2019-09-16 05:01:35', '2019-09-16 05:01:35'),
